item.title: Download and Install
item.description: rust-keylock is delivered as a desktop app, an Android app and a shell app. Here is how you can install what you are interested in: Desktop The desktop application is offered as a Snap, but you may download binaries from the GitHub releases pages. Since version 0.8.0, there are binaries for Linux and Windows. Prerequisites for running the GitHub binaries Java 8 or higher should be instaled in order to run the rust-keylock-ui.
